                  "body": {
                    "type": "TextualBody",
                    "value": "<p rend=\"align(right)\">\n                                        <placeName>Beaufort So. Ca.</placeName>\n                                        <date>Sept. 26<hi rend=\"sup\">th</hi> 1834</date>\n                              </p>\n                              <p>Most Revd. Sir</p>\n                              <p rend=\"indent(2)\">Your fame has travelld. with your work. You are\n                                        known as one<lb/> of the few whose <sic>lifes</sic> have\n                                        been devoted to the <sic>defence</sic> of Judaism: will it\n                                        be<lb/> an assurance for a stranger to ask one question? I\n                                        am a Jew; and thank God[?]<lb/> gloring in being such; not\n                                        one, though, who cares not for the faith; but desirous<lb/>\n                                        of diving into those mysteries, that cannot possibly, by any\n                                        human being,<lb/> to solved; yet, the object, which, some\n                                        may try to obtain. I live in a place not<lb/> much known;\n                                        but whose inhabitants <del>are</del> (excluding Israelites)\n                                        are there [?]<lb/> christians,–that is, members of the\n                                        church; consequently (I am) subject to the utmost<lb/>\n                                        scrutiny, frequently have I been calld. on by some to\n                                        ascertain the general<lb/> belief of the israelites; and\n                                        certainly give such answers as will make to app<lb/>-ear\n                                        their generosity, without regard to prejudice; but often\n                                        have I been asked<lb/> about their saviour: whether we\n                                        believe he has come or not. I answer<lb/> as my parents\n                                        common sense teacher, and the \"Bible\" directs; but\n                                        com-<lb/>monly ask if we believe he has [?] appeared as the\n                                        \"the deemer of mankind\"<lb/> generally. Now all fair persons\n                                        must admit, sir, that what is handed<lb/> down through\n                                        books, excepting those fictitious works that\n                                        extravagance<lb/> will teach us not to believe should be\n                                        somewhat suspected: wed. surely be<lb/> put down by one\n                                                  <sic>incredillous</sic> class if we would not put\n                                        any con-<lb/>fidence in the new testament; yet, a common\n                                        work—an history<lb/> of the revolution—it's contents are\n                                        believed more particularly, as con[?]<lb/> with facts that\n                                        are plainly proven: and what the difference with the<lb/>\n                                        new testament? What further proof is required than that the\n                                        christians<lb/> exist? their doctrine in some respects is\n                                        fair, I mean their inclinations<lb/> to do good; but I want\n                                        to know how the \"Jews\" exist in relation<lb/> to\n                                                  <persName>Jesus</persName>—or Christians. If\n                                        you'll only deign to answer this humble<lb/> request of one\n                                        who values your talents; reveres your name; con[?]<lb/> your\n                                        zeal in behalf of the despised; (though thank God that\n                                        opprobi[?]<lb/>tering is nearly done away with) Revd Sir\n                                        yours c holy <persName role=\"author\">D.\n                                        Jacobs</persName></p>"
                  },
                  "target": "https://colenda.library.upenn.edu/items/ark:/81431/p35t3gr6h/canvas/p1"
                }
              ]
            }
